@node editorsdesk "From The Editor's Desk"
@toc contents
		     @{fg shine}-= From The Editor's Desk =-
		          @{fg text} by: @{"Timo Paul" link timopaul}

This has been a tough month, issue 1 and 2 we were finding out feet, issue 
3 should have been easier.  Life though has a tendancy to get in the way 
of things and putting together this issue was quite stressful if I am 
truly honest.  Finding the time to write up the reviews and tutorials has
meant staying up into the early hours, writing, checking and then editing.
I find it very exhilerating writing the magazine and am always happy to 
see the final product but it is something that keeps me up at night 
sometimes.  Well now that I have that off my chest, on to what you can
expect in this issue.  Sadly @{"Kevin Saunders" link kevinsaunders} and @{"Steve Lord" link stevelord} were not able
to join us for issue 3 but luckily we have @{"John Scolieri" link johnscolieri} reviewing Roadie
and providing a guide on setting up an Internet clock.  In addition we 
have an interview with big time chip producer gwEm, reviews of Roadshow,
Indivision AGA Mk3 and PiMiga 2.0.  I really enjoyed talking to gwEm, he
gave some very interesting answers about his history with making music 
on computers.  The PiMiga was also a lot of fun and has me coming back to
Pi400 more often than before.

During February I have also been chasing up more interviews and have some
fantastic ones already in the bag ready for upcoming issues.  It is such
a humbling experience when talking to other Amiga users and reading 
contributions from people like @{"John Scolieri" link johnscolieri}.  While I may complain about
the the time it takes to put this magazine together I am always warmed
by the people in the Amiga scene.

Well I will quit taking up your time and let you get on with reading the
rest of the magazine.  So grab yourself a hot cup of tea or coffee, or if
you are in a warmer climate, a cold bear or soda and snuggle up to your 
Amiga and enjoy the third issue of @{b}WhatIFF?@{ub}  See you next issue!
  
@endnode


@node news "All the latest news about our favourite computer!"
@toc contents
 	   @{fg shine}-= News and Aminet Uploads for February 2022 =-@{fg text}     

 - = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = -

	     	  @{"  AMINET UPLOADS FOR FEBRUARY 2022  " link aminet} 

Hello fellow users, I hope you have had a nice January, February has been
relatively busy for the Amiga scene.  There have been several software
and firmware updates with new hardware announced as well.  Dig in to see
what happen in Febuary 2022.  In addition you can view all the uploads to
Aminet in February.
 
@{b}Mac Amiga Emulator Update - 1st February 2022@{ub}
vAmiga has now been updated to 1.1beta9 with improvements such as the
hardware config panel haveing been split into separate chipset panels
and a memory panel.  For more info visit: github.com/dirkwhoffman/vAmiga

@{b}AmiLion 1.3 Released - 2nd February 2022@{ub}
AmiLion is an addon for AmiKit providing a variety of wallpapers for 
Workbench and additional Rabbit Hole access to programs such as Firefox,
VLC and Steam.

@{b}NEXT 4.1 TextViewer Released - 2nd February 2022@{ub}
The last update of this versatile text viewer was in 2011 and now eleven
years later we get another update.  NEXT is more than a simple text 
viewer and can be used as an AmigaGuide replacement.  Have a look at NEXT
from Aminet: aminet.net/packages/text/show/NEXT

@{b}Wicher 1211 7-Bit Firmware Update -  3rd February 2022@{ub}
Fixes for RAM controller and asdsan SPI controller tothe Zorro II card 
chain.

@{b}Amiga DOS Creators Interviewed -  5th February 2022@{ub}
The Digital Orphanage have interviewed Dr Tim King and his wife about 
their work on Amiga DOS.  Search YouTube for The Digital Orphanage.

@{b}P96 RTG Updated to V3.2.3 - 9th February 2022@{ub}
Jens has uploaded a new version of the RTG driver with several new 
improvements, among these are: P96 not longer attempts to set the beacon0
register and the vtotal register of the custom chips in case the active
video mode is on at RTG board that isnot in the display chain.

@{b}AmiKit XE Updated to version 11.5+ - 9th February 2022@{ub}
The classy Workbench emulation environment for Windows, Mac and Linux has
been updated to 11.5+.

@{b}Sam460LE Boards Announced - 15th February 2022@{ub}
Production of the new Sam460LE boards will commence soon and pre-order 
alongside.  The new boards are able to run up to 1.1.ghz, come in a Micro
ATC form, include MicroSD slot at the back of the board and come with 
AmigaOS 4.1 FE.  The final price is 735 euros.

@{b}History Of The A1000 Video - 19th February 2022@{ub}
Featuring again in our news section, The 8-Bit Guy has uploaded a new 
video talking about the history of the A1000.  A great video and well 
worth taking the time to check out.

@{b}New Bluetooth Mouse For Classic Amigas - 25th February 2022@{ub}
A new Kickstarter for recreating the classic tank mouse as a bluetooth
device that can be connected to classic Amigas.  It comes in black and
the traditional beige.  The Kickstarter price is 31 euros.

@{b}Apollo V4 Expansion Board - 27th February 2022@{ub}
Quetzal and Owl have created a board in the mini-ITX form that can hold an
Apollo V4 standalone and provide new features and IO ports.

Well that is it for Amiga news for February 2022, if you have anything 
that you would like to be featured in the What IFF? news section contact 
us at: submissions@whatiff.info
  
@endnode

